cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper deals with the problem of semantic segmentation in autonomous driving using a fusion of RGB and LiDAR data. This falls under the intersection of computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) as it involves processing sensor data for autonomous driving. The paper also proposes fusion architectures which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with semantic segmentation which involves natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques.
